UEFI:NTFS — vendored bootloader
================================

This directory is the intended home of the UEFI:NTFS bootloader image that
Ferrus writes to a small FAT helper partition so that UEFI firmware can boot an
NTFS main partition (the strategy Ferrus uses for Windows install media).

