License and GPL compliance
--------------------------
UEFI:NTFS is licensed under the GNU General Public License v3.0. Ferrus is
GPL-3.0-or-later, so redistribution is compatible. To satisfy the GPL when we
ship the binary, this directory MUST also carry:

  1. A verbatim copy of the UEFI:NTFS license (the repo-root LICENSE is GPLv3
     and covers it, but keep the upstream copyright notice here too).
  2. A reference to the corresponding source (the upstream URL and pinned
     commit above), i.e. a clear written offer / pointer to the exact source
     the binary was built from.

Do not add the binary without completing the provenance block and the license
copy in the same commit.
